f other users).  ''What I can''t understand is why Interlisp 10 years ago didn''t have the equivalents of COPY and SWITCH -- both have the same syntax as the the MOVE command (i.e., generalized location specifiers separated by a "noise" word such as TO or WITH).''-----''From': masinter.pa'Date': 13-Apr-84 22':41':20 PST'Subject': Re': for manual'In-reply-to': JonL''s message of 13 Apr 84 18':38 PST'To': JonL'cc': Masinter, LispSupport, LispFriends^''IFY and BQUOTE (like GETD and MAKEFN) are examples of commands that are still quite useful in DEdit, using the control-Z escape.''SWITCH and COPY aren''t very useful in DEdit, which is why I didn''t advertise them.''Larry''-----''Date': 14 Apr 84 13':47 PST'From': JonL.pa'Subject': Re': for manual'In-reply-to': masinter.pa''s message of 13-Apr-84 22':41':20 PST'To': masinter.pa'cc': JonL.pa, LispSupport.pa, LispFriends^.pa''Is the "horse before the cart here"?''IFY and BQUOTE editmacros are not useful if no one uses them.''If the Teletype editor is stil supported (Chapter 17 of manual) then SWITCH and COPY ought to be documented and "advertised".'''Workaround: Test Case: Edit-By: masinterEdit-Date: 23-Aug-84 14':09':32